9
00:00:26,018 --> 00:00:29,601
<i>♪ 'Cause I thought
I was a star ♪</i>

10
00:00:29,842 --> 00:00:31,237
Uh.

11
00:00:31,325 --> 00:00:32,847
<i>♪ How long, tell me how long
can this go on? ♪</i>

12
00:00:32,934 --> 00:00:34,128
Want to get a pizza
or something?

13
00:00:34,215 --> 00:00:35,299
I know a great place.

14
00:00:35,387 --> 00:00:38,130
Well, it's late.
I should, uh, go to sleep.

15
00:00:38,218 --> 00:00:40,051
It's only 8:30
in Seattle.

16
00:00:40,139 --> 00:00:41,549
Yeah, but we're not
in Seattle.

17
00:00:41,637 --> 00:00:44,174
We're in New York,
and we are doing

18
00:00:44,276 --> 00:00:47,947
a complicated surgery on
New York time in the morning.

19
00:00:48,035 --> 00:00:50,408
Okay, fine.
Room service...

20
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:53,705
in bed, then sleep.

21
00:00:53,793 --> 00:00:56,643
We agreed.
Just sex, no sleepovers.

22
00:00:56,731 --> 00:00:57,713
But we're out of town.

23
00:00:57,801 --> 00:00:59,627
- Bend the rules.
- No, it's not a rule,

24
00:00:59,715 --> 00:01:02,369
so much as the basic tenet
of this relationship.

25
00:01:02,457 --> 00:01:04,420
- Which is that it's not a relationship?
- Right.

26
00:01:04,508 --> 00:01:06,713
No complications.
My life is already full of them.

27
00:01:06,801 --> 00:01:09,322
But it's not that complicated.
W-We have adjoining rooms.

28
00:01:09,410 --> 00:01:10,693
They're practically
the same.

29
00:01:10,781 --> 00:01:12,229
And yet,
they are not.

30
00:01:12,342 --> 00:01:13,404
<i>But neurons,</i>

31
00:01:13,492 --> 00:01:16,013
the cells that make up
the brain and spinal cord,

32
00:01:16,241 --> 00:01:17,748
don't regenerate.

33
00:01:17,959 --> 00:01:19,670
I feel used!

34
00:01:20,676 --> 00:01:22,459
Objectified!

35
00:01:22,717 --> 00:01:23,920
Hungry!

36
00:01:24,008 --> 00:01:25,703
♪ And we rage on
till we're blazing in the sun ♪

37
00:01:25,790 --> 00:01:27,451
Okay.
What will it take for you

38
00:01:27,539 --> 00:01:29,005
to let me go to sleep tonight,
guilt-free?

39
00:01:29,092 --> 00:01:30,465
<i>♪ La la la la la la ♪
♪ How long? ♪</i>

40
00:01:30,552 --> 00:01:32,005
Pizza for breakfast.

41
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:33,168
Deal.

42
00:01:33,256 --> 00:01:34,717
<i>♪ And we rage on ♪</i>

43
00:01:34,805 --> 00:01:37,008
<i>♪ Till we're blazing in the sun ♪</i>

44
00:01:41,945 --> 00:01:44,349
I'm still questioning pizza
as a breakfast food,

45
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:46,350
- but this is a really excellent slice.
- Mm-hmm.

46
00:01:46,437 --> 00:01:47,499
How'd you know
about this place?

47
00:01:47,586 --> 00:01:48,709
Mm.

48
00:01:48,841 --> 00:01:50,279
It was part of my wish.

49
00:01:50,619 --> 00:01:52,521
You wished
for perfect pizza?

50
00:01:52,999 --> 00:01:54,372
From a fairy godmother?

51
00:01:54,497 --> 00:01:56,472
Cancer kids who are in
as bad a shape as I was

52
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,739
get wishes.

53
00:01:58,333 --> 00:02:00,044
Osteosarcoma.
Age 10.

54
00:02:00,132 --> 00:02:01,442
Full remission.

55
00:02:02,031 --> 00:02:03,747
What'd you wish for?

56
00:02:04,719 --> 00:02:06,787
- Baseball game at Shea Stadium.
- Yeah.

57
00:02:06,874 --> 00:02:09,099
I got to meet my favorite
player, Dwight Gooden.

58
00:02:09,734 --> 00:02:12,716
I remember thinking,
"I'll be back."

59
00:02:13,216 --> 00:02:15,550
And the next time was with
the Mariners as the team doctor.

60
00:02:15,638 --> 00:02:16,841
That is impressive.

61
00:02:16,928 --> 00:02:18,519
Nothing will beat that
first time out here.

62
00:02:18,606 --> 00:02:20,724
I ate here five times.

63
00:02:20,927 --> 00:02:23,161
Even got a picture out front.

64
00:02:23,318 --> 00:02:24,855
Oh, and there was this
great donut place

65
00:02:24,942 --> 00:02:26,341
right around the corner.
Um...

66
00:02:26,630 --> 00:02:28,091
Gotham Donuts!

67
00:02:28,185 --> 00:02:31,028
Oh! Best glazed donut
I've ever had.

68
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:32,883
That was, uh...

69
00:02:32,974 --> 00:02:35,214
Well, that was our last trip
together before the divorce.

70
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:39,161
Uh, I guess this city
reminds me of better times.

71
00:02:39,966 --> 00:02:43,471
That is the exact
opposite of me.

72
00:02:43,825 --> 00:02:45,012
I grew up here.

73
00:02:45,286 --> 00:02:46,753
Well, not exactly here.

74
00:02:46,841 --> 00:02:49,631
I was like half an hour away
in Westchester.

75
00:02:50,005 --> 00:02:54,927
But my life in New York was
definitely not better times.

76
00:02:56,685 --> 00:03:00,099
Wait. You're saying
we could've had donuts?!

77
00:03:04,879 --> 00:03:07,710
- Admit it.
- 14 blocks was not that far.

78
00:03:07,798 --> 00:03:09,381
And when you walk,
you see things

79
00:03:09,469 --> 00:03:11,285
- you never would have from a cab.
- You're right.

80
00:03:11,372 --> 00:03:13,458
We totally would've missed
that group of mimes

81
00:03:13,546 --> 00:03:15,730
- yelling at each other.
- And the rat dragging the bagel.

82
00:03:15,817 --> 00:03:17,104
That was so gross.

83
00:03:17,192 --> 00:03:18,192
Amy?

84
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,331
Oh, my God!

85
00:03:19,419 --> 00:03:20,354
- Uh...
- Amy!

86
00:03:20,442 --> 00:03:21,997
Nancy!

87
00:03:22,152 --> 00:03:23,659
Yeah.

88
00:03:23,747 --> 00:03:25,292
Nancy Shepherd.

89
00:03:25,380 --> 00:03:27,301
Oh, Amelia's sister.

90
00:03:27,477 --> 00:03:28,760
You must be Owen.

91
00:03:28,848 --> 00:03:30,011
Yes!

92
00:03:30,099 --> 00:03:32,511
This is my husband.

93
00:03:36,149 --> 00:03:37,472
Nice to meet you, Nancy.

94
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,815
I've heard
so much about you.

95
00:03:38,903 --> 00:03:40,675
Do you work here?

96
00:03:40,763 --> 00:03:43,542
I'm covering the chief of OB's
maternity leave.

97
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:44,854
Ironic, right?

98
00:03:44,942 --> 00:03:46,003
How about you?

99
00:03:46,091 --> 00:03:47,128
Everything okay?

100
00:03:47,216 --> 00:03:48,263
Yeah.

101
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:50,597
No...
We're here for a patient.

102
00:03:50,685 --> 00:03:52,253
All the way from Seattle?
Wow.

103
00:03:52,341 --> 00:03:54,051
You must be very
in demand.

104
00:03:54,138 --> 00:03:56,051
I guess that's why
we never hear from you.

105
00:03:56,247 --> 00:03:57,971
Yep.

106
00:03:58,114 --> 00:04:01,171
Been pretty busy
since I saw you last.

107
00:04:01,380 --> 00:04:04,146
I operated on
Catherine Fox herself.

108
00:04:04,234 --> 00:04:05,222
Might've read about it.

109
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:07,143
Also got married.

110
00:04:07,231 --> 00:04:08,261
Aah.

111
00:04:08,505 --> 00:04:10,921
Right. Welcome to the family.

112
00:04:11,161 --> 00:04:13,919
We've got some pretty
deep-seated dysfunction,

113
00:04:14,007 --> 00:04:16,823
but you've probably
figured that out by now.

114
00:04:16,911 --> 00:04:18,435
Ah, what family doesn't?

115
00:04:18,558 --> 00:04:19,849
Do you have sisters?

116
00:04:20,942 --> 00:04:23,628
I do, so I get it.

117
00:04:23,716 --> 00:04:25,052
We should catch up.

118
00:04:25,298 --> 00:04:26,698
Come for dinner,
both of you.

119
00:04:26,786 --> 00:04:28,909
Ah! We can't.

120
00:04:28,997 --> 00:04:30,427
Taking off tonight.

121
00:04:30,551 --> 00:04:31,988
She's got a big surgery

122
00:04:32,076 --> 00:04:33,236
- in Seattle tomorrow.
- I do.

123
00:04:33,324 --> 00:04:34,892
Oh. Well,

124
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:36,511
at least
I got to see you.

125
00:04:36,824 --> 00:04:39,011
Halley's Comet comes around
more than you do.

126
00:04:41,348 --> 00:04:42,956
Oh, uh...

127
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:45,566
call Mom sometime,
kiddo.

128
00:04:45,876 --> 00:04:47,376
It's the kind thing
to do.

129
00:04:50,261 --> 00:04:51,839
Okay.

130
00:04:52,425 --> 00:04:54,183
Thanks for that.

131
00:04:54,298 --> 00:04:55,917
Let's go.

132
00:04:56,971 --> 00:04:58,220
I need to find a shower

133
00:04:58,308 --> 00:05:01,503
so I can wash that "kiddo"
off of me before surgery.

134
