135
00:05:06,846 --> 00:05:09,253
<font color=#FF00FF>*GREY'S ANATOMY*</font>
Episode Title: <font color=#FFFF00>"Good Shepherd"</font>

136
00:05:10,066 --> 00:05:11,841
<i>You got this!</i>

137
00:05:12,050 --> 00:05:13,829
- Oh, man.
- <i>Victory Lane!</i>

138
00:05:13,917 --> 00:05:15,056
- You beat me again.
- No, man,

139
00:05:15,143 --> 00:05:16,243
- you totally threw that.
- <i>Nice race.</i>

140
00:05:16,330 --> 00:05:18,136
Okay, I'm on way too many pain
meds for you to be losing to me.

141
00:05:18,223 --> 00:05:20,011
- Come on.
- Hey, Dr. Lew.

142
00:05:20,099 --> 00:05:22,987
Jonah, these are your surgeons,
Doctors Shepherd and Lincoln. Hi.

143
00:05:23,075 --> 00:05:24,438
- Hey.
- Hi.

144
00:05:24,745 --> 00:05:26,714
- Uh, this is my brother Brady.
- Hi.

145
00:05:27,218 --> 00:05:29,135
You know, I-I would've left him
at home, but he's my ride.

146
00:05:29,222 --> 00:05:30,196
Mm.

147
00:05:30,284 --> 00:05:31,839
Jonah Mays, 18.

148
00:05:31,927 --> 00:05:33,136
He was diagnosed with

149
00:05:33,224 --> 00:05:35,245
progressive kyphoscoliosis
at age 6.

150
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:37,331
He's had multiple
posterior spine fusions

151
00:05:37,419 --> 00:05:39,829
with instrumentation
from T4 to L5

152
00:05:39,917 --> 00:05:40,876
to correct the curvature.

153
00:05:40,964 --> 00:05:43,329
Yeah, it's, uh, pretty much
my entire spinal cord.

154
00:05:43,417 --> 00:05:45,899
I've had... 15 surgeries
in 12 years.

155
00:05:45,987 --> 00:05:48,829
Some due to growth, some due to
the condition's progression.

156
00:05:48,917 --> 00:05:51,181
Yeah, the metal rods bust
right through his skin.

157
00:05:51,269 --> 00:05:52,870
- Can we take a look?
- Yeah.

158
00:05:53,348 --> 00:05:55,041
You're in good hands,
Jonah.

159
00:05:55,175 --> 00:05:56,605
I'll leave you to it.

160
00:06:00,007 --> 00:06:01,618
Looks like the degree
of angulation

161
00:06:01,706 --> 00:06:04,551
- has pushed the hardware off the bolts.
- Mm.

162
00:06:04,638 --> 00:06:06,143
But you... you can fix
that, though, right?

163
00:06:06,230 --> 00:06:08,591
Dr. Lincoln and I will
remove the rods.

164
00:06:08,745 --> 00:06:11,806
We'll insert a nylon tether,
which will stabilize your spine.

165
00:06:11,894 --> 00:06:13,260
It'll allow room for growth,
which means

166
00:06:13,347 --> 00:06:14,696
fewer surgeries
in the future.

167
00:06:14,784 --> 00:06:15,801
Good.

168
00:06:15,888 --> 00:06:18,402
'Cause, uh, you know,
I've got big plans.

169
00:06:18,566 --> 00:06:20,409
I'm moving to California.

170
00:06:20,502 --> 00:06:22,394
I just got accepted
to UC Berkeley.

171
00:06:22,534 --> 00:06:24,345
- Go, Bears!
- Congratulations.

172
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:26,301
- Thank you.
- One, uh... One step at a time, bro.

173
00:06:26,388 --> 00:06:28,530
You're worried.
I get it.

174
00:06:28,777 --> 00:06:30,728
I mean, w-who would take you
to physical therapy

175
00:06:30,816 --> 00:06:32,707
and make sure that you got
to the doctor's on time?

176
00:06:32,794 --> 00:06:33,798
Oh, yeah, that's right.

177
00:06:33,886 --> 00:06:35,366
That's what you've always
done for me.

178
00:06:36,098 --> 00:06:37,455
But I won't need it as much,
all right?

179
00:06:37,542 --> 00:06:38,542
Okay.

180
00:06:38,683 --> 00:06:39,671
We've got
your measurements.

181
00:06:39,758 --> 00:06:41,431
We will be back to
prep you for surgery

182
00:06:41,519 --> 00:06:43,636
- after we compare them to the scans.
- Okay.

183
00:06:44,717 --> 00:06:47,542
Looks like we can use a vats
to anchor the bolts at T3.

184
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:48,672
Just like we planned.

185
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:49,881
Should be done by 5:00.

186
00:06:49,968 --> 00:06:51,930
Ah, that gives us almost
another 24 hours

187
00:06:52,018 --> 00:06:53,930
of observation before
we head back to Seattle.

188
00:06:54,018 --> 00:06:55,421
That's amazing news!

189
00:06:55,509 --> 00:06:57,516
I was just gonna leave you
a note,

190
00:06:57,604 --> 00:06:58,688
- trying to...
- What? What?

191
00:06:58,776 --> 00:06:59,766
Uh, what's amazing? What?

192
00:06:59,854 --> 00:07:02,274
I just heard you say
it's at least 24 hours

193
00:07:02,362 --> 00:07:04,353
till your flight leaves,
so you can come for dinner.

194
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:06,277
John and the kids are upstate
visiting his mom,

195
00:07:06,364 --> 00:07:07,268
so it'll be quiet.

196
00:07:07,356 --> 00:07:08,900
I'll make your favorite
chocolate cream pie.

197
00:07:08,987 --> 00:07:12,719
I... I no longer eat,
um, sugar or gluten.

198
00:07:12,807 --> 00:07:14,801
I'm not taking no
for an answer.

199
00:07:15,038 --> 00:07:16,071
Fine, make the pie.

200
00:07:16,159 --> 00:07:17,159
Good.

201
00:07:17,268 --> 00:07:18,971
Text me when
you're on your way.

202
00:07:19,237 --> 00:07:20,421
See ya!

203
00:07:20,651 --> 00:07:21,878
Can't wait!

204
00:07:24,456 --> 00:07:26,300
So...

205
00:07:26,508 --> 00:07:28,211
you like pie, right?

206
00:07:32,745 --> 00:07:34,723
Five minutes in
the lobby is one thing.

207
00:07:34,779 --> 00:07:36,535
Dinner is a terrible idea,
and I'm not going.

208
00:07:36,622 --> 00:07:38,092
You can't make me go alone...
It's like sending.

209
00:07:38,179 --> 00:07:39,305
Red Riding Hood
to visit the wolf.

210
00:07:39,392 --> 00:07:41,385
I'll be having pizza and donuts
in the city.

211
00:07:41,473 --> 00:07:43,214
- You're more than welcome to j...
- I'm begging.

212
00:07:43,301 --> 00:07:44,659
This is me begging.

213
00:07:44,747 --> 00:07:46,073
Aren't I cute when I beg?

214
00:07:47,497 --> 00:07:50,925
<i>Dr. Kripen, call extension 193.</i>

215
00:07:51,512 --> 00:07:52,721
Okay, Jonah.

216
00:07:52,809 --> 00:07:54,003
Pre-op time.

217
00:07:54,099 --> 00:07:55,200
Are we leaving now?

218
00:07:55,288 --> 00:07:56,698
Why? You winning?

219
00:07:56,786 --> 00:07:59,323
Yeah. But, uh, also...

220
00:07:59,411 --> 00:08:00,590
Brady went
to the cafeteria.

221
00:08:00,678 --> 00:08:02,113
He said he was gonna
go get an apple,

222
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:04,911
but, uh, I guarantee you
he comes back with fries.

223
00:08:05,104 --> 00:08:07,465
You know, we have this thing
about saying bye to each other

224
00:08:07,856 --> 00:08:10,895
ever since our parents died
six years ago in a car accident.

225
00:08:11,122 --> 00:08:12,620
And, yeah,
it was as dramatic and tragic

226
00:08:12,707 --> 00:08:14,114
as your face is right now.

227
00:08:14,317 --> 00:08:16,278
Oh, sorry. I...

228
00:08:16,489 --> 00:08:17,917
I'm gonna give you something
to relax you,

229
00:08:18,004 --> 00:08:20,604
and Dr. Lincoln is going to
mark you for surgery.

230
00:08:20,692 --> 00:08:22,175
Cool. What are you
gonna study at Cal?

231
00:08:22,262 --> 00:08:24,190
Uh, environmental science.

232
00:08:24,278 --> 00:08:25,659
Or literature.

233
00:08:25,747 --> 00:08:27,418
Or something
I haven't heard of before.

234
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:28,721
I-I'm not sure.

235
00:08:28,809 --> 00:08:30,411
Renaissance man.
Nice.

236
00:08:30,528 --> 00:08:32,472
Yeah, well, you know, uh,
knowing what you don't know

237
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:33,588
is the first step
to enlightenment.

238
00:08:33,675 --> 00:08:36,723
You will fit right in
at Berkeley.

239
00:08:36,844 --> 00:08:38,402
So, did you always know
you wanted to be a doctor?

240
00:08:38,489 --> 00:08:40,612
I have four older siblings
who are all doctors.

241
00:08:40,699 --> 00:08:42,899
I'm not sure it ever occurred
to me to do anything else.

242
00:08:43,829 --> 00:08:45,112
Ah, told ya!

243
00:08:45,199 --> 00:08:46,572
Fries.
You want one?

244
00:08:46,660 --> 00:08:47,994
I'm good, thanks.

245
00:08:48,082 --> 00:08:49,697
Uh, but
Jonah's good to go.

246
00:08:49,785 --> 00:08:51,152
Got it, okay.

247
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:52,543
Uh, hold these for me?

248
00:08:52,631 --> 00:08:53,980
Thanks, Doc.

249
00:08:54,542 --> 00:08:56,191
Till next time, brother.

250
00:08:56,613 --> 00:08:58,019
Mm.

251
00:08:58,332 --> 00:08:59,730
Until next time.

252
00:08:59,930 --> 00:09:02,213
Here.
And, uh, take that.

253
00:09:02,301 --> 00:09:03,729
